#### Reading UK Public Health Monitoring Data

The UK government provide some public health data for England (other UK countries have data available elsewhere) on their data portal, here - https://ukhsa-dashboard.data.gov.uk/. The data is available for download in CSV format.

Have a look through the datasets with measurements taken over time which are available on this page. Choose a category, then pick a single dataset where the plot shown is either a line plot with a **single line** or a **bar** plot. Download the CSV formatted data to your computer. You can find these by clicking on the graph then choosing "Download", then "CSV format". Move this file into the `{{< meta practical >}}/data` folder of your `{{< meta git_repo >}}`  folder

In a new Quarto report, `{{< meta practical >}}/ukhsa_data_analysis.qmd`, load this table into R and then view the resulting table with `gt()`. These tables are mostly long, so we can use the `head()` function together with `gt()` to just visualise the first ten lines:

For example:


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
rhinovirus <- read_csv("data/ukhsa-chart-download-rhinovirus.csv")
```

